The paper deals with the Galois hulls of linear codes over finite fields, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the monomial equivalence of codes, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper provides applications to matrix product codes, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
